external_knowledge:
- "shining stars" refers to the breweries that have achieved high ratings;
- "respect of the connoisseurs" and "threshold of excellence" metaphorically refer to the average rating being greater than 4;
- "radiant glory" symbolizes the average rating, which determines the order of the final list.

sql:
SELECT breweries.name, reviews.comment
FROM breweries
JOIN reviews ON breweries.brewery_id = reviews.brewery_id;

SELECT city, state
FROM breweries
WHERE name = '101 North Brewing';

SELECT b.brewery_id, r.comment
FROM breweries b
LEFT JOIN reviews r ON b.brewery_id = r.brewery_id;

